 Seven people have perished after a head on collision between a truck and a bakkie. The seven include the driver and six passengers of the single cab bakkie, which was pulling a trailer. This is the second accident on the Stoffberg road this evening. Another accident occurred between 17:00 and 18:00. It was later observed that a section of tar has been stripped from the road and poses a danger to vehicles travelling at high speed. Motorists are cautioned not to use the R555 until further notice.      Middelburg police officer arrested during Hawks operation Botshabelo’s last song Five busted for dagga Nabbed cops granted bail  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za